body:
- Add timers to record get operations from a Java client
- Tag each timer with region name and result (hit/miss)
- Close existing entries gauge when closing `RegionPerfStats`
- Improve micrometer assertj assertions
- Make public fields immutable on `Get70.Entry`

Co-authored-by: Aaron Lindsey <alindsey@pivotal.io>
Co-authored-by: Kirk Lund <klund@apache.org>
Co-authored-by: Dale Emery <demery@pivotal.io>

The previous PR (#4201) was accidentally merged before all of the tests were passing. It was subsequently reverted. The first commit re-applies the changes from the original PR.

The second commit fixes an issue where `Get70.cmdExecute()` throws a `NullPointerException` when `InternalRegion.getRegionPerfStats()` returns null. The latter method returns null in the case where the `InternalRegion` is a `PartitionedRegion` and its data store has not been initialized:
```
  @Override
  public CachePerfStats getRegionPerfStats() {
    PartitionedRegionDataStore ds = getDataStore();
    CachePerfStats result = null;
    if (ds != null) {
      // If we don't have a data store (we are an accessor)
      // then we do not have per region stats.
      // This is not good. We should still have stats even for accessors.
      result = ds.getCachePerfStats(); // fixes 46692
    }
    return result;
  }
```
